Example from Mithril.js:<p><pre><code>  m(&quot;main&quot;, [
    m(&quot;h1&quot;, {class: &quot;title&quot;}, &quot;My first app&quot;),
    m(&quot;button&quot;, &quot;A button&quot;),
  ])
</code></pre>
React does the same (after the JSX is compiled), and I&#x27;m not aware of any that <i>don&#x27;t</i> just use plain object data:<p><pre><code>  {
    tag: &quot;main&quot;,
    children: [
      { tag: &quot;h1&quot;, attributes: { class: &quot;title&quot; }, children: [ &quot;My first app&quot; ] },
      { tag: &quot;button&quot;, children: [ &quot;A button&quot; ] }
    ]
  }
</code></pre>
Is it just ergonomics, or is there some deeper reason I&#x27;m missing?
